<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<p><b><a NAME="specInv">Is this a Special Investigation?</a></b><br>
<br>
The investigation of allegations which constitute child abuse, neglect, sexual abuse or emotional abuse that is attributable to caregivers extending beyond the traditional parent/child domain.
<br/>
<br>
<p><b><a NAME="malInCare">Is this Maltreatment in Care?</a></b><br>
<br>
A substantiated investigative finding which meets the definition/criteria of child abuse, neglect, sexual abuse or emotional abuse that is attributable to a foster parent, relative or non-relative caregiver or employee of a public or private child caring agency, institution or private residential treatment facility and the victim is a child in the temporary or permanent custody of this state or another state.
<br>
<br>
<p><b><a NAME="policyViolation">Is this a Policy Violation</a></b><br>
<br>
Violations of foster care policies are actions by a foster parent that breach any foster home approval policy or procedure but do not constitute abuse or neglect.
<br>
<br>
<p><b>Concurrence</b><br>
<br>
State Office agreeing with the disposition of the investigation; and State Office agreeing with the action(s) that the county has recommended. 
<br>
<br>
